    The XXAAllllooccSSiizzeeHHiinnttss function allocates and returns a pointer to a
    XXSSiizzeeHHiinnttss structure. Note that all fields in the XXSSiizzeeHHiinnttss structure are
    initially set to zero. If insufficient memory is available,
    XXAAllllooccSSiizzeeHHiinnttss returns NULL. To free the memory allocated to this
    structure, use XXFFrreeee.

    The XXSSeettWWMMNNoorrmmaallHHiinnttss function replaces the size hints for the
    WM_NORMAL_HINTS property on the specified window. If the property does not
